00:01:08.599 --> 00:01:10.140
LAURA LING: And do
your grandchildren

00:01:10.140 --> 00:01:12.090
help you gather the wood?

00:01:12.090 --> 00:01:13.785
MWANAIDI MWENDE:
[NON ENGLISH SPEECH]

00:01:18.180 --> 00:01:21.505
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:01:24.560 --> 00:01:26.310
LAURA LING: This is
one of the reasons why

00:01:26.310 --> 00:01:28.520
so many girls are
not going to school

00:01:28.520 --> 00:01:29.730
and getting an education.

00:01:29.730 --> 00:01:32.520
It's because they're out here
helping their families gather

00:01:32.520 --> 00:01:35.370
wood and other materials
that can be used as fuel.

00:01:35.370 --> 00:01:37.340
And it's a very
clear example of how

00:01:37.340 --> 00:01:41.970
the energy crisis impacts girls
disproportionately to boys.

